<p id="id02371">"What's the number?" the voice demanded. "Your modem."</p>

<p id="id02372">"Ok!  914-555-2190." Scott gave his home modem number.</p>

<p id="id02373">"Be on at midnight."  The line went dead.</p>

<p id="id02374">Scott  briefly mentioned the matter to his editor, Doug,  who  in
turn  gave  him a very hard time about it. "I  thought  you  said
virus hacker connection was a big ho-hum.  As I recall, you  said
they weren't sexy enough?  What happened?"</p>

<p id="id02375">"Eating  crow can be considered a delicacy if the main course  is
phenomonal."</p>

<p id="id02376">"I see," laughed Doug.  Creative way out, he thought.</p>

<p id="id02377">"He said he'd been plowing around NASA computers," Scott argued.</p>

<p id="id02378">"Listen,  ask your buddy Ben how many crackpots admit  to  crimes
just for the attention.  It's crap."  Doug was too jaded, thought
