tions have not been so well received.</p>

<p id="id06876">"We  are actually receiving more help from the public  BBS's  and
local  hacker groups in finding and eradicating the viruses  than
from the NSA or ECCO," said the Arnold Fullerman, Vice  President
of Computer Services at Prudential.</p>

<p id="id06877">AT&amp;T  is also critical of the government's efforts.  "The  Presi-
dential  Order gives the NSA virtual control over the use of  our
